{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"mousey-defective-snail","description":"## Context\nThe domain-separation core: a registry mapping each attestation `kind` to `{scheme, namespace, trust-root}`, pinned out-of-band, so the verifier never selects the scheme from attacker-controlled record data (anti alg-confusion, RFC 8725).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `src/rebar/attest/registry.py` resolves `kind -> {scheme, namespace, trust_root}` from a static policy table, not from the envelope.\n- [ ] `verify(kind, envelope, trust_root)` dispatches on the policy scheme; a test asserts a record whose in-band scheme/keyid is tampered still verifies under the policy-pinned scheme.\n- [ ] Unknown/mismatched scheme for a kind fails closed (test).","id":"518b-0558-fd18-4713","parent_id":"2fd4-baa0-4471-4382","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"attest: scheme registry + per-kind policy table + verify-dispatch"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783735839961631001,"uuid":"e4fb7a23-fb88-4397-a26e-6e9cd5c96452"}